@REM==============================================================================

@node "FAMEFileChecker" "What is FAMEFileChecker ?"

                           @{b}What is FAMEFileChecker ?
                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

FAMEFileChecker is an external process communicating with the @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"},
if the FileChecker process is needed.

FAMEFileChecker is able to check files in background while the upload
continues:-if a file is completely uploaded, FAMEFileChecker will check it.

The user can configure, if they don't like background checking, the background
file check to file check after all files are uploaded.
This mode will also automaticly used if the SysOp does local uploads.

Normally FAMEFileChecker will be used as a background checker, because
this saves lots of time. There is no longer waiting for long file checks
after transfer of some megabytes.

In the next update FAMEFileChecker will also be able to extract file
descriptions (with external tools) and FAMEFileChecker will also be able
to do a background posting of the files if there is a description available.

FAMEFileChecker will execute all files in the directories:

FAME:FileCheckers/FILEIDENT/
FAME:FileCheckers/FILECHECK/

FAME:FileCheckers/FILEIDENT/ is for external File_Id.diz extractor tools.

FAME:FileCheckers/FILECHECK/ is for external file checkers.

In both directories, scriptfiles (script bit set), and executables can be
started.

All scriptfiles/executables will use these arguments:

<Nodenumber> <UserSlot> <Path+File...>

Template for executables:

NODENR/N/A,USERSLOT/N/A,FILEPATH/F/A

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Installation" "How to install FAMEFileChecker"

                         @{b}How to install FAMEFileChecker
                        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

FAMEFileChecker will be automaticly installed if you install FAME.

Normal location of FAMEFileChecker is: 'FAME:Modules/FAMEFileChecker'

In @{"SystemEditor" link "SystemEditor.guide/Main"} -> FAME Modules -> FileChecker Location the location must
be set. Normally 'FAME:Modules/FAMEFileChecker'.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "FAMEFileCheckerUsage" "How to use FAMEFileChecker"

                           @{b}How to use FAMEFileChecker
                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

You have nothing to configure with FAMEFileChecker.

@{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"} is the only program which uses FAMEFileChecker.

@endnode

